PRIVACY POLICY — STORAGE CLEANER
Effective date: May 2, 2026
Last updated: May 2, 2026

------------------------------------------------------------------------

Storage Cleaner ("the App", "we", "us") is a personal productivity
utility that helps users identify and remove large files from their iOS
photo library. This Privacy Policy explains what information the App
accesses, how it is used, and what it does NOT do.


1. INFORMATION WE ACCESS
------------------------------------------------------------------------
The App requests access to your Photos library (iOS Photo Library
permission) solely to read file names, sizes, types, and metadata for
the purpose of displaying them to you within the App.

  - File names, sizes, and media types (photo, video, audio)
  - File creation and modification timestamps
  - Video duration, image dimensions (used for display only)

This data is accessed on-device and is NEVER transmitted, uploaded, or
shared with any server, third party, or external service.


2. INFORMATION WE DO NOT COLLECT
------------------------------------------------------------------------
  - We do not collect personal information (name, email, phone number)
  - We do not collect device identifiers or advertising IDs
  - We do not use analytics, crash reporting, or any third-party SDKs
  - We do not track your usage, behavior, or location
  - We do not store any data outside of your device
  - We do not require an account or login of any kind


3. HOW WE USE THE INFORMATION
------------------------------------------------------------------------
All file metadata accessed from your Photos library is used exclusively
to:

  - Display a list of your files sorted by size
  - Show file type, size, and previews within the App's interface
  - Allow you to delete files you choose to remove

Processing happens entirely on your device. No file content or metadata
is transmitted anywhere.


4. FILE DELETION
------------------------------------------------------------------------
When you delete a file through the App, it is removed using the standard
iOS Photos framework (PHPhotoLibrary). Deleted assets are moved to the
Recently Deleted album in Photos, where they remain recoverable for
30 days before being permanently erased by iOS. The App does not bypass
or circumvent this system behavior.


5. FILES APP ACCESS (DOCUMENT PICKER)
------------------------------------------------------------------------
If you choose to use the "Add Files" feature, the App opens the iOS
system document picker (Files app). You explicitly select files you wish
to add. The App reads only the file name, size, and URI of files you
select. This access is limited to items you manually choose and is not
used to browse your filesystem without your interaction.


6. THIRD-PARTY SERVICES
------------------------------------------------------------------------
The App does not integrate any third-party advertising networks,
analytics platforms, social SDKs, or data brokers. There are no in-app
purchases, subscriptions, or payment systems.


7. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY
------------------------------------------------------------------------
The App is rated 4+ and does not knowingly collect any information from
anyone, including children under the age of 13. Because no personal data
is collected at all, no special handling for minors is required.


8. DATA SECURITY
------------------------------------------------------------------------
Because the App does not collect, store, or transmit any user data,
there is no personal data at risk of breach. All operations are local
to your device and protected by iOS's built-in security model.


9. CHANGES TO THIS POLICY
------------------------------------------------------------------------
If the App's data practices change in a future version, this policy will
be updated and the effective date above will be revised. Continued use
of the App after any update constitutes acceptance of the revised policy.


